{
  "texts": [
    "In practical research, attention needs to be given to the form of the dataset.",
    "The input and output dimensions of the dataset vary depending on the structural parameters and target responses of different metasurface.",
    "One simple solution is to increase the number of samples in the dataset, as more samples imply more features, which can help improve the training accuracy of ML algorithms.",
    "However, in many cases, due to limited sample acquisition or chaotic distribution of data, it is necessary to select suitable ML algorithms for specific problems.",
    "Furthermore, relying on experience or other optimization algorithms to adjust the parameters of ML algorithms is often required."
  ]
}